^B@2hondo717: An unusual auction. It is rare that there is interference over 2@C, but I will discuss one way of handling it. The way some experts handle it is counter intuitive. A pass by me is interpreted as a "waiting bid" same as if I had bid 2@D had pam passed. And a double by me is a bust, saying I have a bad hand, with no aces or kings. So, had Ira and I been playing that a double by me over interference shows a bust, I would have doubled, since I have no aces or kings. The reason for this treatment is that with a bust, the 2@C doubler may decide to leave the double in, if he feels that it is more likely that the overcaller will go down than we can make game. |
